      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SWEET PINS NZ (9) looks close to another win after he finished second last week, beaten just over 2 metres at this circuit and distance. Must overcome a very wide draw but has won from this barrier before and is good enough to beat these if things go his way. OPAL HUNTER (3) made it back-to-back wins at this circuit and distance when proving too speedy for Sweet Pins last week. Led in both of those victories and while he draws a little wider he has enough pace to push forward again so could land the hat trick. DELULU (1) has been performing well from wide barriers this time in. Race fit and better served by the ace draw. MEDIEVAL MAN (8) raced parked but was too good by 2.6 metres at Bunbury last time, giving him two wins and a placing from his last three starts. Draws very wide but is going well.",
